cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about word embeddings, which are widely used in natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new method for learning word embeddings, which involves adversarial training, which suggests that it could also be relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on several datasets, which could make it relevant to categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
